{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":84188,"duration_api_ms":83371,"num_turns":22,"result":"## Scout Report Complete\n\nI've mapped out Milestone 0.5: Agent Output Monitoring And Null-Run Detection. Here's the summary:\n\n**Core Issue**: The current FIFO-based agent monitoring relies exclusively on JSON streaming output for activity detection. When agents run in `--output-format json` mode (which produces no streaming text output), the activity timeout incorrectly kills healthy agents that are silently doing file I/O, causing work to be discarded and false null-run declarations.\n\n**Files Involved** (3 primary):\n- **`lib/agent.sh`** (main work) — FIFO monitoring loop, activity timeout handler, null-run detection heuristics, and output validation\n- **`lib/config.sh`** (minor) — Config defaults already exist for timeouts; may need additional variables  \n- **`tests/test_agent_exit_detection.sh`** — Existing null-run tests; will need extension\n\n**Key Changes Required**:\n1. Add `git status --porcelain` polling to the FIFO read loop to detect file changes as a secondary activity signal\n2. In null-run detection, parse `git diff --stat` to check if files were modified before declaring a null run\n3. Add `CODER_SUMMARY.md` existence check as a completion signal before activity timeout\n4. Ensure file-change detection properly resets the `_last_activity` timer\n\n**Complexity**: Medium\n- **35 coder turns** — Careful integration of git polling into the performance-sensitive FIFO loop\n- **10 reviewer turns** — Validate that git commands are safe, file-change signals work correctly, and backward compatibility is maintained\n- **20 tester turns** — Mock git state, test activity timeout with file changes, verify no regressions in existing null-run detection\n\nThe scout report has been written to `SCOUT_REPORT.md`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"0ce241c4-05ad-4f5e-b983-e9c9a17477cf","total_cost_usd":0.177886,"usage":{"input_tokens"